The paper deals with explaining the predictions of deep convolutional neural networks for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method proposed in the paper involves selecting relevant parameters using Kullback-Leibler divergence, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the interpretability of deep learning networks, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE).
